HEADWORD: Seckel
<hw>Seck"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
small reddish brown sweet and juicy pear. It originated on a farm near
Philadelphia, afterwards owned by a Mr. <etsep>Seckel</etsep>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

